//Create a class UserDetails, two private fields name and Email and pass. Also create public getter and setter methods.
public class Userdetails {
    private String name ;
    private String email;
    private String pass;

    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }

    public void setEmail(String email) {
        this.email = email;
    }

    public void setPass(String pass) {
        this.pass = pass;
    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    public String getEmail() {
        return email;
    }

    public String getPass() {
        return pass;
    }
}
 Step 2 :Create a new class User. Here create a object for UserDetails in main method. On object call method setName() and setEmail() ans setPass() 
 to write values and then call method getName() and getEmail() to read values.
 
 

public class User {
    public  static void main (String args [])
    {
       Userdetails userdetails = new Userdetails();

       userdetails.setEmail("mdacr7@gmail.com");
       userdetails.setName("Imran");
       userdetails.setPass("12emran@");

        System.out.println("Name:"+ " "+userdetails.getName()+"Email:"+ " "+userdetails.getEmail()+"Pass:"+ " "+userdetails.getPass());

    }
}

